06/10/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Former Defence Minister Teodor Atanasiu, suspended by President Traian Basescu because of a criminal investigation, says he will return to his cabinet post once military prosecutors clear him of abuse of office allegations.
Speaking to reporters Thursday (October 5th), Atanasiu said prosecutors have told him the investigation is over and that there are no grounds to launch criminal proceedings.
(Ziua, Nine O'clock - 06/10/06;
Mediafax - 05/10/06)
